review: I can't say enough about Doc Joki. Caring, knowledgeable and a great person to talk to. He made sure he came in during his weekend day off to be there for the birth. I can't say enough about this guy. We feel lucky to have been able to get him.

UW Med is a factory setting, whether by his fault or the industries, it seems like women go through on a conveyor belt and you only get your set amount of time. On a personal level, I never feel like my health concerns are getting any attention. I get all of 2 seconds to express my concerns and begin to describe symptoms and I'm already given a diagnosis. It doesn't seem very personal or caring. I prefer doctors who will consider that my body may react to things differently and that I have logical concerns. I won't be returning to Joki anymore.

Best. Doctor. Ever. I don't even have words to express how wonderful he is. If he retired tomorrow I would seriously rethink having any more children. He made me feel safe and calm throughout my first pregnancy and birthing process.

I can not say enough good things about Dr. Joki. I had a high risk pregnancy and Dr. Joki was recommended to me by many. My whole experience with him was fantastic and I would highly, highly recommend him to everyone. He turned a scary and bad experience into a wonderful experience and I loved my whole pregnancy and delivery because of him. I also know two doctors' wives and met many nurses in the hospital who had chosen him as their doctor and they all loved their experience with him as well. I am also very scared of pain and he basically eliminated the fear and the pain itself. I can't wait to go to Dr. Joki and his staff for another baby!

i cannot say enough about this incredible doctor. he helped us get pregnant after multiple miscarriages and took amazing care of us all thru my high-risk pregnancy. i want to get pregnant again just so that i can see him again ;-)...his staff is amazing as well and truly care about you and what's going on. on several occasions, Dr Joki called in the evenings just to check up on me. i developed HELLP Syndrome at the end of my pregnancy and was in the VERY BEST hands with him and his staff and vast knowledge and also the support of specialists that he works with. everyone at NW always had the same thing to say when they realized he was my doctor "oh we LOVE him". his unique sense of humor, level of care and knowledge are unsurpassed and so welcome and refreshing. he knows to have you write things down while in his office since he is always going a hundred miles a minute! i would, and DO, recommend him highly and would give him TEN STARS if i could!

I expect to try and keep in touch with him and his office staff for many years. He delivered both of my boys and is going to deliver my next in March 2010. When I come for appointments I get a hug and a "how's the family". There have been a couple times in my past pregnancies where I had to go to the hospital for things that have happened. He doesn't even have to be on call, he seems to just always be there! I was sick a few weeks ago and he called me around 8 oclock on a saturday night just to make sure I was feeling better. I love this guy!! After my second son was born, he came in and sat down next to my husband and started discussing football lol I would and DO recommend him to my friends and family with no hesitation!!

I have been a patient of Dr. Joki's for over 25 years. He truly cares about his patients. When my oldest daughter was born 11 weeks prematurely, he came to see her at the UW Hospital even though he was unattached to the facility. He called the hospital to check up on her status until she was clearly out of the woods. I didn't even know about this until one of the nurses caring for my daughter told me. I refer him to my friends without reservation. If I could give him ten stars , I certainly would.

I loved this Doctor. I can't say enough about him and his staff. He delivered my 1st of 3 boys(we moved for the other two)and it was truly the worst thing about moving from Seattle for me. He took very good care of me and even other issues I had at the time that I was having trouble getting other docs to help me with he bent over backwards to help me. He would call me at home on evenings and weekends to check up on me and was just fun to be around with his sense of humor. He's truly passionate and very knowledgeable about his work and patients and that's obvious in his practice. His staff was always kind and compassionate and knew my name from day 1. Personality wise, my husband and I clicked well with him and felt like he always tried to explain the what and why in the decisions he made and answered any questions we had. We have once again moved and I'm now looking for a new OB and having trouble because Dr.Joki is the gold standard to me and they are few and far between.

Dr. Joki has delivered both of my children; I would have another just to see him! Seriously though, in my opinion he has a great, easy going sense of humor that I really click with and need. He can give the initial impression of being too "quick", because sometimes he does talk fast - but I believe it's just him thinking out loud. He is VERY thorough and highly believes in preventative measures, which is wonderful especially if you are in any high risk category. It may take some a little time to "catch on" to his style and quirky sense of humor, but you can tell immediately that he is really a caring and extremely knowledgeable doctor.

Dr. Joki delivered our second baby and we loved the experience with him. He is extremely knowledgable, though to some, might not have the best bedside manners. We really liked him and he impressed us with his level of caring when he would call us during evenings or on weekends to find out how I was doing. Because he works by himself in his own office and delivers almost 100% of his babies, sometimes he runs late. I would definitely use him again.

16 years ago I was looking for a gynecologist and Dr Miller was recommended. He was my gynecologist first and then when I got pregnant, he was my OB. Over the years I have gotten to know Dr Miller very well and I would say, he is the best Dr in town! Not only is he super knowledgeable, but he listens to his patients (and I talk a lot!) and makes them feel heard. He truly cares about his patients and his work. Because Iâ€™ve gone to him for so many years, I feel like he is not only my dr, but he is a friend. I trust him because I know he cares and because he is truly an expert in this field. If you are looking for the best of the best, look no more, you found him!

Dr Miller helped me with an emergency hysterectomy (done robotically). He presented my options in a concise manner weighing all the pros and cons, and I found him to be very practical. I was able to drive after 4 days! He has an excellent bedside manner and a brilliant sense of humor which is much needed during an emergency situation. I would not hesitate for a second to recommend Dr Miller to other women requiring (robotic) hysterectomies.

Dr. Heath Miller performed my emergency hysterectomy and I have never felt better in my life, 2 weeks post-op. His expertise and his bedside manner helped me through a scary day. He also has a sense of humor. Great doc!

Actually I did not find this doctor caring or attentive. I scheduled an apt with him and after waiting 45 min he came in and was disinterested with the pain I had. He requested I do an ultra sound and said he will call me back with results. 2 weeks later and 2 msg still no call. Ultra sound showed I have a hemoraging cyst and I have a lot of pain. I called his office and he was out so another doctor prescribed meds until he is suppposebto call me.

Doctor Heath Miller is caring, very experienced, explains his diagnosis and medical options in a clear and understandable way and is an outstanding surgeon! I came to Doctor Miller for a second opinion as my original doctor told me that my fibroids are too deep for Laparoscopic Myomectomy and advised me a choice of either over invasive surgery or a surgery that is unlikely to cure my excessive bleeding problem. Doctor Miller inspected the ultra sound images and explained that Laparoscopic Myomectomy is the right procedure for my situation, he assured me that he has done it many times and my case is quite straight forward. . He scheduled me for a surgery 10 days later. The surgery and the recovery process was exactly as he described it. My recovery was very smooth. Doctor Miller called me at home to check how I am feeling. The incisions are very small and it looks like they will not leave any scar long term. I feel blessed to be in the competent care of Doctor Heath Miller and will always go to him as my OB/GYN doctor.

Back in 1994 when Dr. Miller was a resident at the U.W. he happened to be the doctor that was on duty when I delivered my daughter and he was incredible. The staff (mostly residents and interns) were making several mistakes and he seemed to be the only one that knew exactly what to do. 19 years later I still praise him. He made me feel safe in the middle of the entire experience.

I love Dr. Miller and his staff, especially Heather. As an older first time mom, with a history of fibroids, I wanted the very best doctor to perform the C section. I asked around the medical community and other doctors, nurses, radiologists and lactation consultants all raved about Dr. Miller. Last week, he delivered my healthy baby boy. It was only later that I found out how complicated a procedure my C Section turned out to be. I definitely chose the right doctor.
Best doctor I have ever had. Very personable and doesn't ever rush you. Simply the best! He has been my doctor for 13 years.

Dr Heath Miller in my opinion is one of the best ob/gyn around and specially if you need a surgery don't look any further. He is knowledgable, caring, compassianate. He makes you feel at ease,listens to you, never makes you feel rushed and if necessary he goes way above and beyond his way to provide you with the best care possible.

Truly one of the kind doctors. I was referred to Doctor Liepmann by another professional for a surgery and I felt blessed that he was my surgeon. Not only my surgery went excellent (with minimal scars that faded very quickly, my recovery has been amazing and I only took Tylenol for a couple of days). I felt like Doctor Liepmann has provided an excellent service with providing a lot of useful information in relation to my condition, communicating with my husband during the surgery. He went above and beyound my expectations by making sure I was going well after the surgery and even giving us his personal phone number in case of complications, which there were none. That's what I call a dedicated professional!
Dr Lieppman has been my doctor for over 20 years. I trust him completely and he is great at answering questions. He pays attention to what you say and gives you options whenever possible.

What a great doctor and nursing staff. So compassionate and sincere. Dr. Lieppman demonstrates such clarity in explaining information and such thoughtfulness and honestly when answering questions. He calls me to give me results, and insists that I call him whenever I have a question or concern. I have never experienced such a kind doctor or nurse. Karen, his nurse, was so kind and even came out to the waiting room to say hello before I went into surgery. I cannot emphasize how comforted I feel by the team. I am so thankful for his expertise and good instincts in finding something my last doctor missed.

I just can't say enough about Dr. Lieppman-he has been my physician for the last 10 years-he is very knowledgeable, really spends a great deal of time talking and never makes me feel rushed-he also has great bedside manner. Last October, my appendix ruptured, and I spent five days at Swedish recovering-I can't tell you how shocked I was when he stopped by to see how I was doing! He is the most compassionate and caring physician and I would highly recommend him.

I have seen Dr. Lieppman for the past 25 years and have gotten the best care I could ever imagine. I work in the medical field and he treats me so good and makes sure that I always understand before I leave and is always willing to answer any questions I might have. He is simply the best.

This will be my 5 the baby with Dr. Lieppman, and my 8th pregnancy. He is very compassionate, and takes wonderful care of his patients. I have recommended him to several of my friends, and they have been very happy with his care as well. His nursing staff is friendly and well educated, they are responsive, and will give sound advice over the phone to the concerned pregnant mamma. I would highly recommend him to any woman for her gynecological, or obstetric needs. Thanks for all the Great care, Seattle Women's Clinic - CDP
dr kipa is compassionate and really helpful. She listens to you and is very friendly. I would definetely recommed her

Dr. Kipa is amazing. She makes you feel like you are her only patient of the day, She takes time to listen, and provides clear, knowledgable detail on your options. She also supports you when you've made a decision. I'm so glad I found her, she's one of the best. And has helped me through a couple tough health decisions.

Dr. Kipa is an excellent OB/GYN. She is friendly, knowledgeable, and has great bedside manner. She really takes the time to listen to you and never rushes with her appointments. In the age where many doctors seem to care only about getting to the next appointment, Dr. Kipa really cares about your whole well-being and comfort. Highly recommend her!

Dr. Kippa managed my pregnancy throughout and did a wonderful job. After complications from c-section performed by a another doctor, she made me aware of my opinions and made me feel confident in her ability to fix the wound. She is very sympathetic and comforting to talk to.
The most amazing ob I've ever had the opportunity of seeing

Dr. Kipa is the most compassionte doctor I have ever met. She took time with me to review my issues. I feel Dr. Kipa is extremely knowledgable and professional in her medical prctice. She took the time to really discuss and elborate on my condtions and them placed me on some medication. Dr. Kipa is not only a great doctor but is also a very kind, genuine person.

Dr. LaGalbo is just an all-around awesome doctor. I have been a patient of hers for the last 6 years and have always had a wonderful experience. She is knowledgable, helpful, friendly, prompt, always gets back to me quickly, and the list goes on and on. She is just fantastic! I have recommended her to multiple people that have had the same great experience.

I started seeing LaGalbo when I moved. She was the first doctor to ever help me with my UTI problems. I ended up having to move away again which was about an hour away. When I got pregnant I drove all the way up there for my doctors appointments. She made me feel so comfortable and made my pregnancy easy. It was worth the drive.

I had been seen by many other doctors for a difficult fibroid/menopause situation. Dr. LaGalbo resolved it short of surgery, listened very carefully, was both highly intelligent and compassionate. She's one of the best doctors I've ever seen.

I can't believe how smart, compassionate, and down-to-Earth Dr. Lagalbo is. She really knows her specialty, and knows how to communicate well with her patients. Her direct approach and honest answers to my questions made me feel like my baby and I were in good hands.

dr lagalbo has been so helpful during my pregnancy and willing to fulfill my wishes during childbirth. i highly recommend her to anyone who is seeking a kind and caring OB who will listen to you and answer your questions thoroughly.

Dr. Lagalbo is amazing. She's to the point knowledgable and will allow you your wishes. I want to have a natural birth and she has so for been great to that kind of way. she had kids of her own naturally so supports the way a womans body is supposed to work.
She delivered my daughter. She's a great doctor.

Nursing staff is great..the Dr Faulkner is rude and arrogant..she not interested in your concerns and is rude...Dr Baldwin is great which is why I stayed or I would have hit the door after first appointment

I came to Dr.Faulkner for a second opinion,she was recommended to me by a friend--she listened to my concerns, examined me and discussed my treatment options.I went for several out patient tests at the hospital and then scheduled surgery. I felt confident in her and her diagnosis, I had surgery ,it went very well, and I only stayed one night in the hospital.She is a wonderful doctor and I am so glad I am her patient. I also received wonderful care at the hospital in Plymouth

Dr. Faulkner,was my OBGYN for many years. She was at each one of my three children births not only is Dr.Faulkner knowledgeable, but she is patient and she listens to her clients. I was very sad when she left the Seattle area. You all are very blessed to have her in Plymouth.Naomi
Excellent, excellent physician who was the first to properly diagnose me.

Dr Faulkner delivered my first child, and if I decide to have another, I'll absolutely go back to her. I wound up having a complicated pregnancy with hospital bed rest, and I found her to be very communicative and empathetic. I agree she can be a bit business-like, but she was always friendly and over the course of my pregnancy I found her to be a warm person. She delivered my baby via c-section, and I have a very small scar, and no complications from the surgery. Her partners and staff are top-notch.

I saw Dr. F for the first time after switching from NW Women's Health where I had been seen for many years. I switched cuz I thought my previous provider (Dr. Levine) was not very thorough for GYN stuff (had been better at OB stuff). Sure enough, on my first visit with Dr. F., she discovered an enlarged uterus, (which likely was present when I had been seen at NW Women's Health?) She referred me for Ultrasound which confirmed a large fibroid. Although I'm glad she was more thorough, I am dismayed in the delay after the US. In fact it has been 8 days since the US, and she has not called me with the results (which the US radiologist told me directly) or her recommendations. Her nurse called on Day 4 (in response to my call), and then gave me bare minimum info, saying Dr. would call me back. Then I got 3 more calls saying that Dr. was unexpectedly out of office. it's been more than a week since the test, and no call from the Dr. I think I'll look for another dr. for fibroid treatmt.

Dr F and her nurse are absolutely fantastic. We appreciated Dr F's directness and she definitely knows her stuff. Her nurse was so genuinely excited and supportive. We would recommend her to everyone and we will use her again.

She was very rushed and did not take a long time explaining things. I inferred about several problems I was having and she found one problem and did not search for any other reasons for the problems I was having. She rushed through my appointment even though I had waited for an appointment for five weeks. She did not seem interested or engaged at all. Also, her cell phone rang very loudly during my appointment...she took the call. It was her nanny. Other OBGYN's I've seen have always told me what they were doing, saying "okay now I'm going to do this, or check for this" but she gave me no warning. Wouldn't recommend her.

I have only seen her once so far, but a friend recommended her and I'm glad she did. I have menopausal issues and she took all the time I needed, she listened, came up with a variety of solutions to try, was very helpful and was overall great. Her nurse was downright fantastic! I will definitely continue to see her.

Words seem inadequate for the gratitude I am feeling after having been led to Dr. Veljovich and his staff - every one of them! Until I was 58 I enjoyed relatively perfect health but in 1998 I experienced a cardiac arrest that I miraculously survived and then in 2004 open heart surgery was needed. So believe me I have had more than my share of Drs. and Dr. offices! I have become very selective of my Drs. in a time in this country that it is becoming more challenging. As an Image Consultant for 22 years I am pretty good at 'sizing up' individuals and it took two tries before I was led to Dr. Veljovich and his wonderful team. My care from the first appointment, through the surgery and now into recovery has been a peaceful experience with perfect results. With every surgery it takes "informed Faith" and there is always risk but with Dr. Veljovich he took me through it feeling confident in his skills. I could feel his care, his commitment to excellence and that he put his own ego aside and my well-being at the forefront. He is truly a gift to humanity and I am so grateful as I recover,
Blessings and gratitude, Dr. Veljovich - and all your staff. My cervix and my heart are happy tonight and thank you! Rachel W.

I sought out Dr. Veljovich for a third surgical opinion, hoping to take advantage of his minimally invasive expertise. He was quite honest in terms of what my options were and what his technological limitations were. I wound up with an open procedure and a large incision - certainly not what I had hoped for. That said, I felt complete confidence in Dr. V, knowing that I was in good hands if my fears of cancer and/or complications came true. That was a huge relief for me going into the OR. Office visits seemed rushed, and I was not very happy about that. Having spent my career in the operating room, I had more questions than he had time to answer, but at 7 weeks post-op, I'm happy that I had no complications. I'm grateful to have had an excellent surgeon to care for me during a very emotionally devastating experience.

My PCP referred me to Dr. Veljovich in October 2013. From our very first consultation with him, he inspired confidence in his ability to deal with my health challenges. Despite a waiting room filled with patients, he took the time to answer all our questions and put our minds at ease. He met with my husband and me just before I was taken into surgery, and brought comfort to our hearts at that critical juncture. His high level of technical expertise, combined with his sincere compassion for the well-being of his patients, were major factors in the positive outcome of my case. In addition, everyone we came in contact with at Pacific Gynecology Specialists were sincerely helpful and concerned with our well-being. Without reservation, I highly recommend Dr. Veljovich to others.

Best experience I have had with a doctor. Compassionate, caring and made my experience comfortable. Couldn't have ask for a better doctor. He more than took care of my issues and I am very very pleased. Would recommend highly to anyone looking for treatment.
My former OB/Gyn oncology surgeon referred me and I have found Dr. Veljovich very helpful. So far, he has done checkups and referrals as needed.

If you're looking for someone who is an expert in his field and highly competetent, this is your doctor. He is amazing. If you're looking for warm-fuzzies and mediocrity, he is not for you. He is an excellence-driven doctor and I had 100% confidence while in his care.

Dr. Veljovich is an impressive robotic surgeon and oncologist. As a registered nurse, I was very pleased with his knowledge and skill as well as his bedside manner. As top specialists generally are, he is very busy and your appointments are brief, but he will take time for any questions you have and explains things thoroughly. He did not remember the specifics of my case each visit, but I didn't expect him to with the number of referrals he handles. I accept the responsibility for being in charge of my health care. Once we started speaking and he reviewed my record, he would remember the specifics. He did a very complex 5 1/2 hour hysterectomy for me due to cancer using the Da Vinci robotics and I was up walking comfortably and able to discharge within 18 hours of leaving recovery. Impressive. And I did not experience any complications or infections. I was also very satisfied with his nurse, Heidi and Swedish Hospital where he practices.
Saw Dr. Veljovich for a few months. I had to remind him what occurred at the previous appointments and he was not consistant with his recommendations. Found another physcian that has be great.

I was referred to Doctor Veljovich from another doctor. Those doctors send you to Dr Veljovich because he is the best. He has been with me since day 1 of my cancer issues in more than one reproductive area. I have been a patient of his for over 4 years. There is no other doctor I would ever trust, he knows what he is doing and there is not words to express his compassion and knowledge. He truly cares about his patients- his assistant, Heidi is amazing too. I know that my health and my future are ok because of the care I have received from Dr Veljovich and his team. I'm due to have surgery again, and I know I'm in good hands with him. If anyone is being referred to him from another Dr be thankful, he truly is the best.

I was fortunate enough to be referred to Dr. K when I first moved to Seattle several years ago - and followed her to her current practice as well. Although I moved out of the Seattle area a couple of years ago, I still travel back to Ballard for my Gynecological appointments because of the positive experience I have had with Dr. K. Dr. K takes the time to listen and provide wonderful guidance and I've never felt rushed through the appointment. I have never experienced an extensive wait and the office staff have always been genuinely pleasant to work with. Quite simply, Dr. Knickerbocker always shoots you straight, provides a comfortable and respectful health-care experience, and even adds a little humor to each visit. I have always felt that Dr. K truly cares about her patients and I have found her "bedside manner" to be just right. What more can a patient ask for? I recommend Dr. K for anyone looking for a wonderful Gynecologist in the Ballard / Seattle area.
Dr. Knickerbocker delivered both of my children and she was incredible! I loved my prenatal care with her too. Highly recommend her!!!

When I was pregnant the 1st time, 13yrs ago, I needed a dr. that would see me even though I wouldn't take a blood transfusion in an emergency (religious beliefs). She was the only one, after searching through many dr's that wanted to see me. I ended up having a c-section with my 1st (fetal distress). When I got preg. 17mths later, she had asked me if my religious beliefs had changed and if I was willing to accept a blood transfusion? I told her my beliefs had changed, but that I would really like, not to have one. She was very supportive and didn't object. She was pro VBAC, but as I approached my due date, I wanted another c-section. Once again, she was supportive and honored my wishes and scheduled the c-section. My son decided to come 2 days before the c-section and she let me decide whether I wanted to still have the c-section or try the VBAC. I had the VBAC and it went great! I am trying to get pregnant again and I will definitely be making the drive to go and see her again.
I absolutely loved her! Awonderful doctor and a great person.

Dr. Knickerbocker is great. Sometimes Ive had to switch appointments because she is busy, but overall Ive always had a wonderful experience. Her office staff is particularly friendly and welcoming as well.
I will not see anyone else after my first exam I trust her expertise, and her knowledge of women's hormone replacement is refreshing and evidence based

Love Dr. Mihalov. She's so sweet. I'm sure that she has plenty of other people in rooms/waiting to be seen, but she always makes me feel like I'm her most important patient. She's never in a hurry to move on to the next person, and always has time for me and my questions :) I went in not knowing what I had after putting up with discomfort/pain for several months, and she diagnosed me as having a dermoid cyst, and advised me to get it removed right away. They were able to schedule me for surgery the following week, and it was so simple! She told me at my follow up appt. that my dermoid cyst was one of the biggest ones she'd ever seen! They said they removed almost 2 liters of fluid from it before removing it altogether. Yikes! My scar is healing nicely and looks great. Very clean job. If she were a general practitioner, I would go to her for all my doctor appointments! Thanks to her, I'm back to being a healthy 20-something. She saved my life. I could not have gone on living like that!

I came to Dr. Mihalov after a horrendous experience at the University of Washington's Hospitals and Clinics. I found her to be concerned,knowlegable, and professional. She took a lot of time with me and understood my need for reassurance and information. I highly, highly recommend her. I only wish I had gone to her first.

I have endometriosis I have been having pain since I was 14 I am 25 now I went to Dr Mihalov in 08. Dr Mihalov is the best Dr I have had for this I have been to sooo many to help me with this and all they told me is I cannot handle pain. When I went to Dr Mihalov she told me we need to do a Laparoscopy to see what is going on I was diagnosed with endo. People with this need to know that it can come back fast or take years it up to your body. My pan is doing better then what I had beforeThe only way for your doctor to know for certain that you have endometriosis is by looking inside.

I have had painful periods since I was 12. I took dr. m's suggestion and went in for a laproscopic pro. She said she removed ALL OF THE ENDO. By the way, they got me out of recovery so fast @ VM that I wasn't able to pee and had to go in for an emergency cath. I NEVER healed from surgery. In fact, i developed extreme pain 24/7. I had cramping and pain in my left ovary (the one she worked on) so bad I was bed ridden. She said that this was not her goal of surgery and didn't know what else to do. I ended up going to cali to a specialist. He said that my ovary was so BEAT UP he was shocked. He said, "she needs a little more education in order to be doing surgery." He said that the endo was stage 4 and that there is no way she could have removed it all. It couldn't have come back that fast, from the time of the surgery to the time I saw him. He helped me with 50% of the pain Dr. M CAUSED. I'm in my 20's and can't do anyting i used to. My life is very limited.I'm grieving my old active self
Virginia Mason along with Dr. Mihalov are very poor from a customer service standpoint. I chose to go for a second opinion and now have switched Dr.'s.
Dr. Mihalov is an excellent surgeon who has a gentle and kind bedside manner.
Dr. Mihalov is SOOOO WONDERFUL!!!!! She is sweet, caring, compassionate and she TRULY CARES about her patients!!! I TOTALLY RECOMMEND HER TO ANYONE needing a WONDERFUL OB/GYN!!!!

Dr. Uhlir had known me when she was with Pacific Gynecology when I was going for in vitro with one of her partners. I knew eventually I would have to have a hysterectomy due to my horrid endometriosis I had for many years. We got to know each other during my fertility treatments. When it came time for me to have a hysterectomy - I already knew who would do the surgery - Dr. Uhlir - she is warm, funny, thorough. I give her 10 starts out of 5 stars.
Dr. Uhilr is the best! she treated my infertility problem

Awesome, she did an abdominal myomectomy on me in 2007. The surgery was a success; no significant blood loss, never a concern about having to covert to a hysterectomy, healed well with no complications, etc. I wish that she was still practicing, she accepted an administrative role for the women and infants center at Swedish.

Dr. Uhlir is the BEST RE! Not only was she amazingly knowledgeable but she was also friendly and made sure that either she or her staff were always available. She also helped us emotionally by keeping a sense of humor through it all. We had several complications but I never felt rushed or like we were a bother. She (and her staff) took very good care of us. I'm glad we were successful (we're pregnant!) but I miss seeing her!
The very best in Seattle. Busy yes, but takes time with you. Very knowledgeable, trustworthy, kind, gentle, informed, honest. Staff great too. If you can get to see her, don't hesitate.
VERY BUSY BUT ON TIME AND VERY ATTENTIVE, REASONABLE AND SENSIBLE. HAS HELPED ME VERY MUCH.
Dr. Cho is only interested in women who are pregnant. She also left her practice and didn't even bother to contact her patients. She is not a nice person or a very professional doctor.

I love the ob who delivered my now 4 year old grandaughter- her name is Dr. Cho - and she practices at Northwest Hospital --- I also went to her ( I'm 64 and no longer need to ''ob part- lol) because my family doctor wanted me to wait months before they would schedule a routine pap--- come on, folks - all I needed was a good gyn-- and she is great - nice staff, too--.
Blessings,
( she was fabulous when my grandaughter was born- my youngest was SO stressed out and anxious - her husband was about to return from his first deployment to Iraq - --- and without the kindness and tact of Dr. Cho - I think my poor child would have been a mental case)
J.- aka- Old Mom

Dr Cho delivered all my children and most of my family members and office co-workers go there. She is so kind and is able to solve most difficult problems. She does not hesitate to refer me to other sub specialist with high risk problems.

Dr. Cho is amazing! I felt comfortable explaining what had been going on. Her nurse is great too, and even gave me M&M's afterwards. Not sure what kind of speculum she used, but it wasn't uncomfortable at all and I didn't feel a ton of pressure like I usually do. The one thing I hated was the recto-vaginal exam. OMG! so painful and uncomfortable. The nurse in the room had to remind me to breathe.

I went to see her, and the doctor was very rude. Extremely rude. She wouldnt even allow myself to explain my problems thoroughly and kept cutting me off. Whether she's intelligent or not, I dont know, but I'm certain she's a rude and arrogant person who doesnt care for her patients. A doctor should be caring before anything.

Dr. Cho is a great doctor. She has helped me thru 2 of my deliverys and I am due with my 3rd in the fall. She is always willing to spend time to answer my questions fully. Her staff is nice and very helpful. It is not a pain to get an appointment. I have not had to wait long in the lobby. I have recommended Dr. Cho to several of my family and friends. They love her too.

Dr. Cho has delivered both my daughters. Unlike some physicians, she didn't just show up for the last few minutes. While I was in labor, she checked on me repeatedly-even in the middle of the night. And the prenatal care also was excellent. She answered questions, supported my decisions, and always seemed happy to see me. Her office staff also is friendly and organized and never kep me waiting.

Dr Wells was on call the day my twins were delivered, though she is not normally my doctor. I had one high risk baby who was a footling breech necessitating an emergency c-section due to water breaking. Dr Wells was waiting for me at the drop off zone, took charge and knew exactly what to do. She and one other OB had my babies out within minutes of arriving at the hospital by ambulance safe and sound. She was my breech baby's advocate checking me right there in the drop off zone, getting me into the knees to chest position (yelling at the paramedics for having me in the wrong position) and getting me into the OR in minutes. Both girls came out great and she sewed me up perfectly with no further complications. She talked me through the surgery, was very caring, and came to check up on us afterwards. I felt like I was in the best possible hands at that moment and am grateful to have had her.

I can't speak to how Dr. Wells functions during pregnancy, but I can't say enough good things about her with respect to my delivery. I was not her patient (I was with a team of midwives), but shortly after my son was delivered, I hemorrhaged and nearly died. Dr. Wells and the staff at Evergreen Hospital saved my life. I am eternally grateful to her for that. She was calm and kind, and I was very lucky to have her available that day.

It was my first baby and she didn't help with my questions at all. She was never on time. Most often she was more than 60 mins late. She always forgot details about my case and asked me the same questions over and over again. She botched my c-section and I had to stay back 2 weeks in the hospital. You need to stay away from this doctor. I liked her nurse during my pregnancy. She is kind and helpful.

Dr. Wells made me feel very comfortable in her office- I almost forgot I was getting a pap smear! :) She is always on time, her staff is excellent (love her nurse!), she is always ready to answer any questions I have. I especially like her because she is very kind and gentle. I would recommend her to anyone. She knows her stuff!

Ann Bridges does not have deep knowledge in her field and more concerned about the payment rather than her patients' health. She does not read patients' medical histories and does not listen to them carefully trying to establish the reason of a condition. I have had her as my provider for a couple of years and after I realized that she is a failure as a professional, I was happy to switch to a different gynecologyst. Do not waste your time if you care about your health and look for a doctor elsewhere.

I had my first visit with Dr. Bridges, I feel shes very knowledgeable, but don't have time for her patients, don't read their charts before the actual visit, too rough!!!!..ive had make doctors with huge hands that were gentle.shes rushing to get to next patient, (more money greed)focus too much on payment type. Sense prejudice, which is sad, we dont condone prejudice in Seattle. I immediately changed doctors. Sound like she was upset that my husband and I waited til the age of 42 to have another child, I thought that was my choice.

She is wonderful! I felt very comfortable with her, right off the bat. Friendly and didn't seem rushed, thorough. When I went back, she took the time to review my chart before coming in. It bugs me when the doc comes in and downs down to your chart as if they have no idea who you are or what your history is. Very professional.

I have been seeing Dr. Bridges since about 2005/6. She is always very chill, laid back and always seems like she has a ton of time. I was surprised by some reviewers who didn't feel this way, but my experience with other doctors was more rushed and like I always asked too many questions which I have never experienced with Dr. Bridges. She is awesome and I recommend her HIGHLY!

Dr. Bridges was my dr. for my first 2 pregnancies. I think she is a very smart dr, but I felt rushed in my appts. At one point one of her office staff told me she only could spend 10 min with me even though my appt was scheduled well in advance because that was the maximum amt of time Dr. Bridges had for every appt. In my first pregnancy, Dr. Bridges could not find my son's heartbeat at 12 weeks. The best the Polyclinic could do was send me home and schedule me for an ultrasound in the late afternoon the next day. The next 24 hrs was excruciating. After a post-delivery problem with my 2nd child, that Dr. Bridges couldn't find yet my current dr found in 5 min, I decided to leave. That problem required follow up surgery so it wasn't a little issue that would clear with time. Overall I think Dr. Bridges is smart & caring, but perhaps subject to organizational constraints on her time that impact patient care. Try drs associated with Overlake - you'll be happier.
Dr. Bridges is a great doctor--she's very competent and warm without being unprofessional, which is how I like doctors to be. Her nurse is great, too. I haven't been to a better doctor in Seattle.

I have been seeing Dr. Bridges for over 10 years. She saw me through two pregnancies while she was preganant herself. She delivered my second child and also helped me with laser surgery on abnormal cervical cells. She is very personable, compassionate, warm and knowledgable. I highly recommend her and she has had her LPN for as long as I have been a patient, she is also great.

I haven't been to Dr. Bridges in a few years, but I remember her to be very patient, very educated and sometimes late, but then that's a doctor thing anyway. She has a huge client base, so it's hard to get in to see her. She does the most thorough breast exam of any doctor I've been to. She is very calming. (I have a tremendous fear of doctors and she has never made me feel like an idiot because of this irrational fear.) I would definitely recommend her as your primary OBGYN doctor, especially if you are having issues.

Dr. Bridges seems very knowledgable and experienced in her field. Her staff however, isn't the best. Her LPN always messes up my blood pressure checks, which can be dangerous since I have hypertension. Her front-desk staff are rude high school girls who talk loudly about their daily dramas. I feel like this clinic and the doctor is quite impersonal, and I definitely feel like I am just a number... I've been going there for 7 months of this pregnancy, and they still cannot pronounce my name correctly. Aside from that, Dr. Bridges is sweet, seems caring, and is non-judgemental... not too mention being very well educated and knowledgeable. It is sometimes hard to get ahold of her or the nurse... it sometimes takes 2-3 days before they finally return my phone calls.
She listens with respect to everythig you have to say. She never makes you feel she needs to rush to the next patient. She's wonderful!!
Dr. Friele makes you feel completely comfortable. She's great!
Dr. Friele says what she means and treats her patients with a high level of respect.

I actually read these reviews before seeing her, but chose to focus on the positive reviews as well as her credentials. Now I really wish I had listened to all the warnings because they were spot on. Dr. McLennan was one of the worst doctors I've ever seen. Her bedside manner was appalling. She was arrogant, rude, and barely let me get a word in. It was very bizarre. I might have put up with it if she were a competent doctor, but she seemed insecure and contradicted herself many times. Needless to say, I do not recommend her. I found a new OB-GYN and my experience with the two was night and day.

I just had my first baby a week ago and Dr. McLennan was the best OB I could have imagined. I have a slight fear of doctors and avoid checkups and hospitals whenever possible but with it being my first pregnancy I knew I had to be tough. Dr. McLennan and her staff eased my fears and took excellent care of me the whole way through. I always felt she was concerned about me but more importantly, he health of my baby and every test/result was explained thoroughly so we never worried unnecessarily. I felt Dr. McLennan was extremely professional and will definitely be keeping her as my OB for our next baby!

By far the worst OB I have had. I went to her after suffering a bleeding episode in the first trimester with my fourth baby. She was very arrogant with both my husband and I. Not willing to answer questions or hear us out. The delivery was horrible as she kept trying to order more interventions without explanation. Finally, she went off duty and we ended up with Dr. Brown delivering our daughter! He was wonderful...I would highly recommend him as an OB.

Dr Mclennan was my ob for my 4th child.After the delivery I suffered for months having trouble going to the starting and stopping urine, leakage at inconvienet times and difficulty going # 2. I also had red blood everytime I went.I called the office right away and was told this was normal in some cases and continue to do my kegels. I came in at my six week and still had issues. Dr M reccommended I see a GI.All results came back normal.I went back to Dr M she said continue with kegels. I said the problems still persist. She said well things change when we have children especially with so many. I have lived with this disorder for three years I finally went back to the ob who delivered my first child and was diagnosed with a cystocele and rectocele. I want to have the surgurey and move on with my life. I wish I would have gotten a second opinon at the time.I feel this doctor is inexperienced and does not acknowlegd her patients symtoms.I would not reccommend this doctor to anyone.

I saw Dr. McClennan while she was still with Women's and Family Health in Renton when I was pregnant with my son last year. I had had two miscarriages beforehand and was nervous about the pregnancy which required me to take several medications and had been labeled "high-risk." I saw Dr. McClennan many times. She was quick and smart, but I found her bedside manner to be very frustrating. There were several times I was told I was too anxious and that I would likely suffer from postpartum depression. When my husband came to an appt she ignored him completely. Two weeks before my due date she left WFHS and I became a patient of a different doctor. He was so understanding and accepted my anxiety as a first time mom who had had two losses. I couldn't believe how relieved I felt to have a doctor who respected me instead of telling me how neurotic I was. So... Dr. McClennan is not someone I would go back to see.
I too am trying to find her, please let me know where she is practing currently. I also want to move to her new practice.

She is the Best Dr. that I have ever been to, Personnable, poilte, easy to get to know, and she really cares about you as a person. Now that she has left Women's and Family Health Specialist in Renton I'm trying to find out where she went as I will follow her!! Does any one know?

THE BEST OB!!! Dr. McLennan has been my OB for the past 6.5 years. She has always given me great advise & takes the time to really listin to my quesitons. I have recomended her to several friends & they all love her!

Very abrasive, arguementative. Unprofessional. Very knowledgeable but is so unprofessional I will not return. Difficult to obtain test results. I eventually had to see another clinic and have tests repeated just so that I could get the results. A doctor who is not afraid to be belittling and rude.

Dr. Gorenberg was extremely friendly and wonderful to work with. He answered all of our questions and acted like he had all day with us. He is a bit weird and I could see that horrible rating being true, but that's because that person just didn't get to know Dr. Gorenberg in the right forum. He is an amazing doctor and yes, does add humor to his work - that's probably what he meant in that previous bad rating. He is very knowledgeable in what he does and did my surgery flawless too.

Dr. Goreberg delivered our first son in 2009. My wife's condition placed us in high risk. He was the on call surgeon and I must say he performed absolutely superbly. This was a risky procedure navigating around large intrusive fibroids and he made it look like a walk in the park. It turns my stomach to read the other review of him. Based on how well he took care of us we sought him out for our second birth. Dr. Gorenberg saved her life and the life of my newborn. Our new son Max had his umbilical wrapped around him 3x in the womb. My wife's complications produced a severe blood loss. Dr. Gorenberg was extremely professional throughout. His quick but careful actions saved my son and my wife's. If you are looking for a seasoned professional then look no further. Everyone we spoke with at Swedish 1st hill said the same thing - we had the absolutely right person in the O/R that day! No one would ever be able to take that away. HE was the right man, twice! Mark and Jennifer C

Horrible bedside manner.Made a scary situation WORSE by his tone and personality. Would NOT recommend seeing this dr for any reason. Dr's should handle medical information-esp.scary scenerios- with tact and compassion. Dr. Gronenberg did neither. In fact, he inflamed the situation with his tactless delivery. His last words to me were "Sorry for all the drama, but I'm an OB. Drama is the name of the game." That is most certainly NOT the sentiment that I wish for my OB to view his or her profession with. I am sorry that I had an encounter with him (the only reason I did was bc it was a rush medical procedure that I was having and he was the only dr available - and now I know why. No one would see this man when they had other options). He truly escalated my emotions when they did not need to be. The situation was stressful enough without him dramatizing them. I urge you to seek another dr if you happen to be faced with seeing him.

Dr. Ou did my stand alone tubal on april 29, 2005. I am forever greatful! He was knowledgeable and is an excellent surgeon! I had the surgery on a friday and I was back at work on monday. I've never wanted kids and he set me free! Highly recommend!

I had a large ovarian cyst that needed to be removed. I saw 2 other obgyns and both freaked me out telling me i had 60% chance of ovary removal. Dr. Ou was recommended by a friend, and did excellent surgeries her friends too. He told me 99.9% I can keep my ovary. He performed my operation and it has been 2 years. I recently did another pelvic ultrasound and everything looks good... no scar tissue either.
The smartest and best doctor ever. I just love her and the staff that works with her
Dr Goff saved my life. I am so glad that I left Swedish and come to the University of Washington
Dr. Kulgren is personable, approachable and caring. Very diligent, and forthright in her communication. I would still see her if I hadn't had to change insurance.

Dr. Kulgren was critical and diligent in her research regarding my test results, made it easy to understand why she was making the recommendations she did, and worked with me to form a plan. She's an excellent ally, and I'd be glad to recommend her to anybody. If you're in the Seattle area, go to her.

It is possible that Dr. F is/was a good baby doc or doc for patients that need someone who firmly appears to know their topic, rather than actually know it. Going to her my experience is: she does not listen to the patient and tends to apply what has happened to her, to you. Even though she told me over and over that each woman'd body is unique and that she would listen to what I told her about my body and involve me in the decision making process, she didn't. She reversed herself repetitively on topics, decisions, and medications, always insisting that whatever she had abruptly changed her mind to was *best*. This included medication levels and treatments (I would leave the office believing I was getting a particular prescription and suddenly find that it was switched to something very different). She was pushy, aggressive, and dismissive. It may be that she is/was a good baby doc in some situations, but I would not recommend her to anyone.

I cannot say enough good things about Dr. Frankwick. She has seen me through an emergency c-section, 2 miscarriages, outpatient surgery, and a VBAC. Her emotional support and ability to remain calm in all situations, as well as her willingness to take the time to answer all of my questions make her a true treasure in my mind. I've never had a doctor who would personally phone me if I called into the clinic with a question, and I have had multiple phone conversations with her. The nicu nurse told me they consider her one of the most intelligent OB's on staff, and multiple other medical doctors have sung her praises to me over the years. She is amazing.

I agree, she is very knowledgeable and trustworthy. However, her staff do not return calls when they say they will and it is difficult to get in for an office visit during what I considered to be an urgent situation.

I 've seen her 17+ years, never met a more knowledgeable & more competent doctor,had one ovarian surgery, had to see different doctors before I was finally diagnosed by her, also saw me thrue all my pregnancies (all difficult pregnancies) had 2 emerg. c-sections performed by her, she saved my little boy, If it had not been for her expertise, quick performance and knowledge I don't think he would be with us. Had one recent experience (my third pregnancy) which was a life/death situation was hospitalized for a few months, she could not continue treating me because i had to be seen by a team of doctors that specialized in these type of pregnancies was very scared to see other docs & having to depart from her but i trusted she knew what she was doing & she put me in the best of hands considering my situation & even though she could no longer continue my case she kept up to date with my situation & never felt that she abandoned me. I owe my life & the lives of 2 of my kids to her. been blessed
I have never been more confident in a doctor's knowledge and expertise!
As a RN who works in obstetrics, I have seen Dr. Frankwick in a variety of situations, both personal and professional. In my opinion, they don't get any better than her!!!!
A knowledgeable and competent doctor, but she's rather stiff and difficult to relate to.

I was referred to Dr. Hipps and I think she is a wonderful dr. She has taken very good care of me, is very gentle in her examinations. She has always been very kind to me and my family. I have had some scary things happen and she is very competent and caring.

I tried to get an appt. with this office but was not able to get in because the staf said my medical records had not been received yet. After several calls back and forth I found out the records had never even been requested and that as a favor to me they would ask Dr Hipps to see me. It was their fault to begin with and then made it seem like she was doing a huge favor accepting to see me. I have a bad taste in my mouth about SCCA now because she was the GYN they recommended. I never met her but some of her office staff are not very organized and I am going to call UW Women's Clinic instead.
Dr. Hipps was thoughtful and attentive; however, the surgery she did on me was and continues to be problematic. I feel she did not take responsibility for that.

Competent, Caring, Compassionate Physician. She is amazing. She is the most personable and warm physician I have ever had care for me. I am so thankful she came into my life at this time. Her staff mirrors all of her good qualities.

Awesome Doctor and awesome treatment. Cancer is frightening enough, so a really great doctor is so very important. Dr. Hipps is above and beyond being just a good doctor. She is great. Caring campassionate and more than competent. She did a surgery that most doctors **** women when they have to do it. Not my words, just the words of others who have had the same surgery. My surgery was 1000 times successful. The after-care has been just as good. If you have been diognosed with a gyn/cancer and you live in washington state, check out Dr. Hipps at Seattle Cancercare Alliance.
She is a butcher. Not a doctor. Get her out on the medical profession.

She has been my doctor for over 3 yrs and delivered my son. I love her up beat and up front nature. She was amazing during my pregnancy and I was so lucky to have her on call when I went into labor. She is a knowledge doctor and was supportive of my decision not to be induced when my due date came and went. I went into labor right at 42 weeks (although we had scheduled an induction) and she was there with me every step of the way to deliver my baby.

Dr. McDermott was on call when I went into labor (not my chosen OB). Her manner was impatient and brisk. I felt rushed through the labor, interventions insisted upon in the interest of speeding things up. She insisted I have an epidural so that she could cut my cervix to promote dilation, all of which led to more interventions; forceps, vacuum, and the threat of C-section because I "wasn't pushing well enough". My labor and delivery was a bitter disappointment, and I felt very poorly served by Dr. McDermott.

She's been my OB for 5 years. I think she is awesome! I've recommended her to many of my friends already. She's got a spunky personality, but is always professional. I've had 2 healthy pregnancies under her care. I've also had the unfortunate experience of having a miscarriage, which required a D&C. Dr. McDermott was so encouraging through it all, and helped me move past it and stay upbeat.

Dr. McDermott doesn't remember what she tells you she will do or have done. We were in the hospital with complications early in the pregnancy and she came for a check up in the room. She couldn't remember the ultrasound results from that day and told us she would let us know what they were when she came to see us the next morning. She never came to see us the next morning or the entire day. She said she would write an order for medication but never did. She later said she would have an induction scheduled for when she was on vacation but none of the on-call doctors would go along with her plan because they said it was not safe for baby or mother. She had my wife have an amniocentisis done so that an induction could be done the next day. My wife went through a painful amnio and was told she would be induced. The amnio was a complete waste of time, pain, & money because Dr. McDermott couldn't do the induction per hospital policy due to how far along my wife was in her pregnancy.

I saw her for several years for semi-annual appointments. She was really upbeat and helpful. After two years of seeing her twice a year I started to notice she didn't remember who I was, and would tell me oh we'll do that next time, and I would have to remind her she said that last time. She was always late. I've waited for an hour or more everytime I go in. I was 15 minutes late to an appointment with her and I was her last appointment of the day and she wouldn't see me. I decided to stop seeing her at that point. Can't imagine seeing her if I was pregnant. Would not be fun.

Dr. McDermott was on-call during my delivery. As labor wore on there was poor communication throughout the day. Suddenly after 26 hours in labor she told me I needed a c-section, despite the fact that I was previously told that we wanted to avoid a c-section because my low platelets. When we asked about the change in plan she got defensive and after a near-shouting match basically ended up saying "because I said so." She was condescending. The incision from the c-section wasn't dressed properly and never healed. I had to get a second surgery (from a different doctor) to fix it.

Dr. Mcdermott removed an ovarian cyst that was causing problems. The surgery was successful, however, she did not explain what was going to happen or where my incisions would be. She also told me that part of the purpose of removal was to send the cyst to pathology to see what it was. At my post op she told me she had not done pathology on the cyst because she knew what it was; an endometrioma. Then she wrote in the post op report that it was a hemorrhagic cyst, not endometriosis. I am still trying to figure out which it was, but because she didn't do pathology, though she told me she would, I still don't know exactly what caused all of this. My new doctor said he post op report was vague and cyst should always be sent for pathology. I am not going to her again and I wouldn't recommend her to anyone else.
I left Dr. McDermotts office. She was fine until I had a miscarrage then acted very strange. More looking out for herself than me.

I only saw Dr. McDermott briefly. Her nurse practitioner, Jenny Howarth, misdiagnosed a yeast infection as a severe case of genital warts. She pulled in Dr. McDermott who agreed that it was warts but said it was too severe to operate on. They prescribed a cream instead. I was troubled about their diagnosis, and when I came back the next day to ask more questions, I saw Jenny who got very defensive, refused to answer my questions, and finally said 'nobody's perfect' and I was welcome to go find another doctor. She pointed out that Dr. McDermott hadn't even billed me for her time. I don't mind paying for a professional and I would much rather be charged for someone's time than left to an incompetent assistant. When I saw another doctor, it turned out that I didn't have genital warts at all. My skin had turned white due to a combination bacterial and yeast infection, and after using an antibiotic for 5 days my color went back to normal. Thank god they didn't try to operate on me.
Please be aware this doctor will make you so uncomfortable! I did not enjoy my visit or will ever trust this doctor again

Dr. Blackham is an amazing doctor! He is a great listener, very attentive to his patients, and is almost always running on time. He delivered both of our kids, and honestly I don't think that either experience could have gone any better.

I had Dr. Blackham for all three of my kids. I live in Bellevue so I could have found someone else after my first but loved him. He was so knowledgable, kind, had a sense of humor and he plays the guitar for you after you have your baby!!

Exceptional! I cannot say enough good things about my experience with Dr. Blackham. From answering my many questions at the beginning of my pregnancy, to teaching me stretches to help prevent tearing, to helping aid in a wonderful labor experience. Iâ€™m a first time mom and initially had a weird experience with a different doctorâ€¦.being referred to Dr. Blackham was a God-send. I highly recommend him.
Great interpersonal skills, very knowledgeable and explains procedures accurately, fantastic nursing staff. She has to be the best OBGYN I have ever seen.
Great OB-GYN doc, very kind & knowledgeable. Excellent nursing staff at clinic.

Dr. Agress is my favorite OB so far. He's very knowledgeable, compassionate and has a great sense of humor (I find it comes in handy when your feet are up in stir ups:). I had a D&C with him with no complications at all. Great doc!

Dr. Agress was one of the best doctors I ever had. He delivered my second and third children. Big difference between the doctor of my first and Dr. Agress. I was going thru a divorce during my 3'd pregnancy and would go in and cry each visit. He was very caring and compassionate. Has a great sense of humour. With my 2'nd pregnancy, I had begun with another doctor, who, when I started bleeding vaginally and wanted a note to stay home from work the rest of the pregnancy(working on my feet, lifting heavy objects, etc.)(had a miscarriage shortly before and was worried that I'd have another one) laughed and told me that if stress could cause a miscarriage then all teen moms would loose their babies. Left her and went to Dr. Agress. He said that if a woman felt that she couldn't work, he'd support her and give her a note. I also had had a C-section(1st baby) and had been told that I would have to have one all future pregnancies. Dr. Agress let me try and have a vaginal birth. Very patient.

Dr. Agress was not my OB, but was the OB on-call when I delivered. In my opinion, he appears to be an excellent surgeon and is very well-suited to deal with emergency situations which one may encounter during labor/delivery. However, I felt that his bedside manner had something to be desired and I felt like my long labor was holding him from some other more important pressing matter.

I absolutely love Dr. Sorenson! She had cared for me and my three deliveries of 4 children and saved my life when I went into cardiac arrhythmia with my first born and could not consider going anywhere else for my following pregnancies. I was considered high risk every time. she delivered my first child and my second pregnancy of twins while also training a resident at the time. She was out of town for my last delivery but called me the following morning to congratulate me. She is the absolute best and can not explain in words how much of a difference it made in mine and my children's lives that she cared for us during my pregnancies.

Dr. Sorensen is a perinatologist/ maternal-fetal medicine specialist, meaning she specializes in complicated/ high-risk pregnancies and deliveries. I was seen by her throughout my pregnancy and found her to be warm, compassionate, knowledgeable, and up on current research and practice. She listened carefully to my concerns and was thorough in addressing them. The only downside, which she was very upfront about, is that she is a part of a very large practice meaning that, if they are managing your full care and you do not require a scheduled c-section or induction, any one of about 10 doctors could be the one on-call for your delivery.
Dr. Shope is the best doctor I have ever seen! I would consider having another child just so I could be seen by her again. lol! She really cares and takes the time to listen and help her patients.
Dr. Shope is wonderful. She listens to your concerns, takes her time in talking with you, and is exceedingly compassionate.
She delivered my baby after a complicated induction and labor. She's wonderful!!

Wonderful Doctor...everyone in the office is nice and courteous. The other doctors in her practice are also very helpful. Me and my baby would not be alive today if it was not for her. I highly recommend her for all obstetric and gynecological needs.

She's very respectful of her patients, always treating them like intelligent people and not just a collection of symptoms. Allows the patients to make choices regarding their own healthcare. Not the typical big-headed ego I've grown to expect of doctors.

My experience with Dr. Patani was through the ER when admitted for excruciating pain. The gastro team didn't know what was going on and Dr. Patani quickly admitted me suspecting uterine fibroids. I've seen other reviews that she has less than desirable bedside manner. Dr. Patani may not be a touchy feely sort of doctor, but she knows her field well. That is what matters most to me. Thank you, Dr. Patani for your help.
-I. Gonzales; Seattle, WA

I love Dr. Patani! She has always been very real and down to earth with me. She is like talking to a friend. She also seems to know her stuff and I have confidence in her medical knowledge. I will keep coming back.

I went to this ob/gyn.. Doctor. Dr. Patani. She is very kind and compassionate. I think I might be a few years older than her. I think she's a very young new doctor. And is timid. But there is nothing wrong with being young or timid at all. And she's better than doctors I've seen that are forty years older than her. I mean she the smartest new doctor I've ever seen. No complaints here at all. What a great doctor she is!
Dr. Patani was had poor communication skills and was not willing to listen to my questions. I will never return to her office.

It was the worst appointment and exam I have ever had, and what was sad is that is was by a woman.She was short, rude and had very poor bedside manner. Apparently she had to be somewhere else, she obviously saw me during rounds or something. I have only had amazing doctors at Minor and James, she was the opposite, she really tarnishes their reputation.

I had a first visit with Dr. Patani in the summer of 2012. She had an emergency and the staff instructed me after I was in the waiting room that she would be late, which was ultimately fine. I did have to get back to work for a meeting so had some time to wait and told the staff how long I had. I also asked if I should reschedule and was told no. When the Dr. arrived she was abrupt and seemed in a rush. She did my exam and without my query she started making recommendations for me to change to a new birth control and seemed annoyed by my questions and my desire to know more before taking on her suggestions (I have been on the same product for years with no problem). She left the appointment by telling me to set up an appointment for the product/procedure she was recommending. I was incredibly put off by our interaction - she was quite rude. I still use this office but will be trying a new doctor.
Not compassionate, patient care is not an individual approach

Teresa Patani has been super helpful with all the health issues I've been having. Her office is easy to get a hold of and I've never had a problem getting a appointment. She always has time to sit with and talk over issues with me. Not pretentious at all- I first thought she was a nurse because she was pretty laid back.
Plain rudeness And no manners. with a bad attitude!!

I was 39 weeks pregnant with twins. My other OB surprised me by leaving for vacation, but didn't tell me until 8 days before. I was not satisfied with "on call" options, as I was not given any answers when I asked about their twin or breech experiences, and I was not encouraged to meet any of them (there were only 4 others in that practice). I did not want to induce. SO I switched to a midwife the day of my labor, and Dr Dimer was the attending OB. Midwife delivered the first baby vaginally, and Dr Dimer did a SUPER FANTASTIC footling breech extraction of baby B, at 6 lbs-9 oz (bigger than Baby A). She was so calm, cool, collected, didn't interfere with my concentration. She allowed dim lights in the OR, a birthing bar, me laboring on hands & knees, and even Robozo positioning! An AMAZING OB!!!! I'm so grateful she works with this midwife, I could not have asked for a more experienced, calming, confident and kind provider. Thank you, Dr Dimer!

I had been seen by several doctors before who didn't really know how to treat my condition. At my first visit w/Dr. Dimer she had a plan for me within minutes! I like that she LISTENS to her patients, shows genuine concern and takes the time to answer questions. Sometimes she is booked up, but she is worth the wait! I'm very pleased with the services I've been receiving from her.
She is thoughtful, knowledgeable and very thorough and best of all, always listen to my concerns.
Dr. pray is amazing. She will discuss anything you want with her and she is so comforting. My roommate randomly found her online and referred me to her. Now my sister and I both go to her.

Sheâ€™s my current OB for my first pregnancy! Sheâ€™s a total sweetheart. Very funny, listens to all of my problems/symptoms & treats accordingly. Recommended a different course of treatment for my heartburn, calmed me down about several of my anxieties. If you donâ€™t like her, it might be a you thing. The first appointment is a little awkward, but after you warm up to each other, everythingâ€™s great! Hopefully sheâ€™ll still be around for baby #2!
I loved Dr.Vasavada.. she was amazing. I was also really lucky she delivered my baby:)

Dr. Vasavada was on time for my dr's appointments. However, she was not very personable, nor did she fully answer my questions to my satisfaction. She seem very timid in her job field and I had difficulties relating concerns to her. Additionally, it was difficult trying to get a hold of her for results of my lab tests, and she did not return my calls in a timely fashion. I would not recommend this doctor in the future to my friends or family members.
Please do not go to Dr Norland. She seems very easy going, but there is a flip side to that -- not being thorough or careful.
Dr. N spends time getting to know her patients and making them feel comfortable. She is absolutely amazing and listens to her patients about what is going on with them. Highly recommend!!!
I loved having Dr. Norland as my OB. I was TERRIFIED when I had my daughter and she was so supportive. I also really connected with her nurse/assistant and enjoyed my visits with both of them.

I was looking for a new OBGYN because I wanted to get prgnant and I had a strange ultrasound a couple years back indicating I might have PCOS. I "interviewed" Dr. Norland and she was very upbeat and positive encouraging me that everything will be fine. I wanted to believe her. I had my annual with her and I asked to see the ultrasound of my ovaries. She blew off my request saying everything was fine. I finally went to a fertility doctor because I wasn't having normal cycles and sure enough I have PCOS and it's very obvious on the ultrasound. Dr. Norland didn't even look at it! Would not suggest seeing her if you want someone that's going to listen to you. Plus her nurse is not engaging nice or friendly.

Dr. Harvey is knowledgeable I am sure, but she has a set mind of her own. When I tried to ask about labor preference at 20 weeks to determine if she is a good fit for me, she refused at first, saying it's too early to discuss labor.
When I told her I would like to avoid epidural as much as possible, she indicates epidural is the medicine to go and continue saying that is the appointments afterwards. I indicated I do not want IV put in the second in got admitted into the hospital, she went on and trying to tell me it is the standard procedure and it is "just" for easy access. I feel like she has a set mind of her own and it is hard to get my preference to her. So I decided to switch provider who I can communicate better.
She does not pay attention to my problem. Optimistic. I will consider another doctor next time.
Dr. Harvey is wonderful. I had an ectopic pregnancy last year and she and her assistant supported me through it like no other. I will definitely go back once I get pregnant again.

overall, personally, as a woman who has never been pregnant before and had tons of questions, she made me feel stupid for asking anything. and to top it off - she wasn't there for my daughters birth... but i guess that should have been expected... because she wasn't there for the majority of my monthly appointments. Oh! and her nurse, told me i had gained too much weight too fast - how much weight did i gain? 35 pounds total! long story short... Susan Harvey ruined my first pregnancy experience, and I will never 0 never! go back. She sucked.

While I love my doctor, Dr. Van Blaricom, I've grown increasingly frustrated with their office experience. And frankly, if she wasn't so darn good, I would have switched doctors a long time ago.
CONS
1) It is incredibly difficult to get an appointment with a doctor. They book out months in advance, and you'll often be directed to work with the nurse practitioner. As a non-pregnant patient, it appears to be even more difficult to get in with the doctor.
2) Be prepared to wait a long time. It gets busier and busier...my last couple appointments have resulted in long waits, the most recent was one hour, after which I had to leave and reschedule due to a work commitment.
3) It's hard to get someone to respond to you, over the phone or email, especially outside of office hours. There is no voicemail, unless you have an emergency. So if you need to cancel, change or request an appointment, this must be done during office hours over the phone, as there is no online scheduling capabilities. However, the office does confirm appointments via email. But they do not reply back when you respond to those emails, so don't expect to get a hold of anyone.
4) There's no cancellation list. So even though the office knows there's a demand to get patients in, they require patients to call daily to see if there are any cancellations.
Long story short, customer support is lacking greatly, with the exception of Rosalie the office manager. While I can understand being busy and in demand, it appears that some better systems should be in place and perhaps additional staff should be hired.
PROS
Both doctors are extremely knowledgable, kind and caring. If you actually get an appointment with them, you'll be pleased once you are in the room with them.
Rude, uncourteous staff. Billing questions take forever to answer. It seems like staff gives preferential treatment to certain patients. Wait time often over 45 minutes. I would not go back.

Dr V was not my Dr but did deliver my daughter. It was my first pregnancy and I was very upset as was my husband that we waited at least 25 minutes for her to show up to the hospital so I could deliver. When my daughter was born she came out blue and not crying. All the Dr said was " It's normal, it's okay" but nothing was explained to me and I was scared to death. She did not come back to check on me during my stay nor did she follow up once I left the hospital. I found a new OB and I am happy to be out of there!

While Dr. V herself is very knowledgable and helpful and always has a smile on her face, you will never see her. The last time I went in her nurse practitioner spent 20 minutes on her iphone trying to figure out facts about the birth control I was on. If you want to make an appointment with her be prepared to wait over a month. You will wait in the office well over your appointment time to be seen and this morning I've been calling since they open (8:30 and it's now 9:15) and the phone as remained unanswered. They don't allow you to leave messages either so if you have a busy work schedule good luck getting anything done on time. The staff is extremely unprofessional and I have yet to make even the semblance of a personal connection with anyone on staff. Overall her staff is careless and inconsiderate. I'm switching doctors as soon as possible.
I delivered my daughter with this doctor and had an awful experience. She was extremely too nonchalant about everything.

For those of you who are 1st time mothers looking for attention & guidance, Dr. Vanblaricom may not be the right choice for you. She has established a system where she is barely ever in the office, and her staff & nurses take care of most issues on their own. When you're pregnant for the 1st time, scared & confused, you need professional attention directly from the doctor. I ended up miscarrying with an ectopic pregnancy, and the staff was very unprofessional. They would forget to call me back w/my lab results & they would fail to explain risks in detail. I should say that Dr. V herself is incredibly knowledgeable and professional. However, she's barely around & you will most likely never deal directly with her. I stuck around until the pregnancy ended, but I'm going to a new OB now that we're trying again. Don't be fooled by her gorgeous office with an ocean view - I fell for it too, but in the end I realized I needed someone who cares about my health & will take the time to meet me.

I absolutely love Dr. VanBlaricom. She is patient, clear, and knowledgeable. Her staff is nice, but nothing spectacular hence the rating of 4. I've never had to wait longer than 5-10 min for my any of my appointments. When my son was born, Dr. VanBlaricom came in at 10:30pm on her day off to deliver my son! She was the rock that kept it all together. There was a nurse that was getting on my nerves, and I think she was getting on Doc's nerves too. But she kept her cool, and when it came down to the last leg, she took charge, got me to focus on her, and got the job done. I live 25 miles away, but it's worth the drive.

Dr. Vanblaricom is super nice, but beware, she is part of a "on call group" so there is a chance she will not be there to deliver your baby, and this was not disclosed to us EVER until the big day. I come from a very conservative family and have a very conservative Husband and we were very upset that it was some male doctor whom we had never met or heard of before that showed up for my delivery.
